DocConstant.Name: BOLT
DocConstant.Documentation: A solid or hollow cylindrical structural element installed in the ground through drilled holes to reinforce and stabilise the ground through tension in the bolt. The bolt usually includes an anchor plate with bolt and is bonded to the ground either by a mechanically expanding end anchorage, friction along its length or grouting along its length. It is generally untensioned, but may be tensioned if required.
